107 (j) Premiums for medicare supplemental insurance policies may differ between persons
108 who qualify for medicare who are 65 years of age or older and those who qualify for
109 medicare who are younger than 65 years of age; provided, however, that such differences
110 in premiums shall not be excessive, inadequate, or unfairly discriminatory and shall be
111 based on sound actuarial principles and reasonable in relation to the benefits provided.
